Cybercrime Case Study – Phishing Attack

Phishing is one of the most common types of cybercrime in which attackers try to steal personal information by pretending to be a trusted person or organization. These attacks usually happen through email messages, fake websites, or mobile messages.

In a common phishing case, a student receives an email that looks like it is from a bank or online payment service. The email asks the user to click on a link and enter login details. The link opens a fake website that looks exactly like the original one. When the user enters the username and password, the attacker gets access to the account.
Many people lose money because they do not check the website address before entering their details. In India, phishing attacks also happen through UPI messages and fake customer care calls.

This case shows that lack of digital awareness can lead to serious financial loss. Users should always verify links, avoid sharing OTP, and use secure passwords to stay safe online.